  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We discuss the ground state energy, E ( g ), of some anharmonic oscillators p 2 + x 2 − 1 + P ( x , g ), where P ( x , g ) is a polynomial in x and g . Included is an example with a convergent perturbation series converging to the wrong answer and counterexamples to Dyson's argument on instability implying the divergence of perturbation theory and to the assertion that terms lower order in x to the same order in g do not effect the asymptotics of the perturbation coefficients a n as n → ∞.</subfield>
